  "title": "Income pooling strategies among cohabiting and married couples",
  "abstract": "Studies explaining why cohabiters are more likely to keep money separate than spouses have mainly focused on selection processes, without taking into account the heterogeneity within both union types in levels of commitment. Cross-national studies are rare",
